briefTitle: Comparison of Three Batches of the Japanese Encephalitis Vaccine IC51

eligibilityModule.eligibilityCriteria:
Main Inclusion Criteria:

* Male and female subjects aged at least 18 years with written informed consent and either no childbearing potential or negative pregnancy test

Main Exclusion Criteria:

* History of immunodeficiency or immunosuppressive therapy, known HIV, drug addiction including alcohol dependence

outcomeMeasures.title: GMT for Anti-JEV Neutralizing Antibody
outcomeMeasures.description: Equivalence between batches with regards to GMT (Geometric Mean Titer) was postulated if all three pair-wise 95 % Confidence Intervals for GMT ratios were between 0.5 and 2.

outcomeMeasures.title: Safety
outcomeMeasures.description: Safety laboratory parameters, rate of SAEs and medically attended AEs, systemic and local tolerability

outcomeMeasures.title: SCR for Anti-JEC Neutralizing Antibody Titer
